title: macbook 12 inch 2015, a1534 sudden dead
message:
visually, there's no liquid damage..
r4750 looks bad, but when i measure it, it still has 20v on ppdcin
i have ppbus g3h is 8.6v
but PPVIN_G3H_P3V3G3H is 20v, shouldnt it be 3.3v ? is the bad r4750 causing it ?

title: macbook 12 inch 2015, a1534 sudden dead
message:
PPVIN_G3H_P3V3G3H comes from PPVIN_G3H, so 20V is correct!
It powers up the 3V3_G3H power supply.

Do you get all S3/S0 voltages?
However, I do not recommend to waste time on this board.
It will end with dead CPU, like all A1534.
You can try to reflow entire board, just for test.

title: macbook 12 inch 2015, a1534 sudden dead
message: How many amps? Sounds like CPU died like always
